<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880624-0133 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: H.H. Robertson's Heermann Resigns from Executive Posts </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RHH WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   H.H. Robertson Co. said Beverly G. Heermann, president of its Cupples Products division and a corporate vice president, has resigned from both posts, effective June 30.    Frank Roland, a corporate senior vice president, said Mr. Heermann and H.H. Robertson had &quot;a mutually agreed parting.&quot; He declined to elaborate.    Reached at his home in St. Louis, Mr. Heermann, an H.H. Robertson employee for 35 years, said he agreed with Mr. Roland's statement and wouldn't comment further.    H.H. Robertson, an international construction firm that makes metal building components, said Mr. Heermann was succeeded by Thomas Turzak, who had been vice president of operations for the Cupples division. </TEXT></DOC>